05505nam a22006975i 9780823292622DE-B159720230103011142.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230103t20222011nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a97808232926227 a10.1515/97808232926222doi  a(DE-B1597)566118  a(OCoLC)1306540767  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY 7aREL0000002bisacsh1 aBartholomew, Ecumenical Patriarch, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aSpeaking the Truth in Love :bTheological and Spiritual Exhortations of Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew /cEcumenical Patriarch Bartholomew; ed. by John Chryssavgis. 1aNew York, NY : bFordham University Press, c[2022] 4c©2011  a1 online resource (464 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aOrthodox Christianity and Contemporary Thought00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tForeword -- tPreface -- tIntroduction -- t1. Patriarchal Proclamations: Encyclicals for Easter, Christmas, and Great Lent -- t2. Patriarchal Exhortations: Addresses to Orthodox Hierarchs and Faithful, Clergy and Laity -- t3. Ecumenical Addresses: Presentations at Ecumenical Gatherings -- t4. Academic Discourses: Occasional Lectures at Scholarly Institutions -- t5. Messages and Declarations -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe second of three volumes of His All Holiness Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomew’s writings, this book includes a selection of major addresses and significant statements by the “first among equals” and spiritual leader of the world’s 300 million Orthodox Christians. Whereas the first volume covered global and interfaith issues, this volume represents the inter-Christian initiatives and theological outreach of the Patriarch, covering a range of topics, such as ecumenism and theology. It also contains various ecclesiastical declarations, such as occasional pastoral encyclicals and extraordinary patriarchal exhortations. His All Holiness was trained and experienced in inter-Christian relations, having pursued studies in Roman Catholic theology at the Gregorian University of Rome, Protestant thought at the University of Munich, and the ecumenical movement beside the World Council of Churches in Geneva. Moreover, he has lectured widely on the significance and role of Orthodox theology in contemporary society, having received honorary doctoral degrees from esteemed academic institutions throughout the world. Unafraid to address sensitive, and even controversial issues – such as papal primacy, divisions within Christianity, and inter-Orthodox unity – His All Holiness balances Orthodox doctrine and canon law with open-mindedness and open-heartedness. His official visits to Rome as the personal guest of Pope John Paul II marked the first occasions in history that an Ecumenical Patriarch met with the Roman Catholic Pope in Rome. His invitation to Pope Benedict XVI marked the opening of the Pontiff’s ministry and his first visit to a Christian minority within a Muslim nation. Over the last two decades, he is also the first Ecumenical Patriarch to have traveled throughout the world and to have convened meetings of all Orthodox primates of autocephalous Churches as well as of all bishops directly within the Ecumenical Patriarchate. This book reveals the spiritual depth and profound doctrine of the Orthodox Church from the unique perspective of a Christian leader speaking the truth in love.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh1 aChryssavgis, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChryssavgis, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWilliams, Rowan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package